etariat/files/honorary_degree_by_convocation_0.pdf |format=PDF |title=Honorary Degree Conferred |website=Uwindsor.ca |accessdate=2016-02-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128063612/http://www.uwindsor.ca/secretariat/sites/uwindsor.ca.secretariat/files/honorary_degree_by_convocation_0.pdf |archivedate=2016-01-28 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web4.uwindsor.ca/units/law/newschannel/archives/newsF10.nsf/inToc/B3B8841A062562658525773100700C9D?OpenDocument |title=University of Windsor - Law - Breaking News - Chief Justice McLachlin to receive Honorary Degree |website=Web4.uwindsor.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''2010''' || [[Ryerson University]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ryerson.ca/calendar/2014-2015/pg1511.html |title=Ryerson University : Ryerson Honorary Doctorates and Fellowships |website=Ryerson.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Nova Scotia}} || '''2010''' || [[Cape Breton University]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbu.ca/honorees |accessdate=May 1, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503135110/http://www.cbu.ca/honorees |archivedate=May 3, 2015 |title=Honorary Degree Recipients &#124; Cape Breton University - HAPPEN.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbu.ca/honorees/beverley-mclachlin# |accessdate=May 1, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102064932/http://www.cbu.ca/honorees/beverley-mclachlin |archivedate=January 2, 2015 |title=The Right Honourable Beverley McLachlin &#124; Cape Breton University - HAPPEN.}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''2011''' || [[Queen's University at Kingston|Queen's University]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.queensu.ca/secretariat/senate/honorarydegrees/MasterList.pdf |accessdate=May 1, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427124758/http://www.queensu.ca/secretariat/senate/honorarydegrees/MasterList.pdf |title=Honorary Degrees |archivedate=April 27, 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Quebec}} || '''June 2011''' || [[Concordia University]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.concordia.ca/mclachlin |title=Honorary Degree Citation - Beverley McLachlin &#124; Concordia University Archives |website=Archives.concordia.ca |date=2000-01-07 |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''26 October 2012''' || [[University of Western Ontario]] || [[Doctor of Civil Law]] (DCL)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uwo.ca/univsec/pdf/senate/honorary/honorary_degrees_by_year.pdf |format=PDF |title=The University of Western Ontario : Honorary Degrees Awarded, 1881-present |website=Uwo.ca |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''2012''' || [[Lakehead University]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D.)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lakeheadu.ca/sites/default/files/uploads/22/Honorary%20Degree%20Recipient%20List%20-%20Updated%20January%202015.pdf |format=PDF |title=Honorary Degree Recipients |website=Lakeheadu.ca |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Scotland}} || '''2014''' || [[University of Edinburgh]] || Doctorate<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scripts.sasg.ed.ac.uk/registry/Graduations/GraduateDetails.cfm?ID=3431 |title=Honorary Graduates of the University of Edinburgh |website=Scripts.sasg.ed.ac.uk |date=2000-01-07 |accessdate=2016-02-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304065444/http://www.scripts.sasg.ed.ac.uk/registry/Graduations/GraduateDetails.cfm?ID=3431 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Quebec}} || '''2015''' || [[Bishop's University]] || [[Doctor of Civil Law]] (DCL)  <ref>https://www.ubishops.ca/event/donald-lecture-series-the-right-honourable-beverley-mclachlin-p-c-former-chief-justice-of-canada/</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''31 May 2016''' || [[Laurentian University]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D.)  <ref>https://laurentian.ca/news/six-distinguished-canadians-receive-honorary-doctorates</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://laurentian.ca/stub-204 |title=Archived copy |access-date=October 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013132838/https://laurentian.ca/stub-204 |archive-date=October 13, 2018 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Quebec}} || &nbsp; || [[Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Massachusetts}} || &nbsp; || [[Bridgewater State University|Bridgewater State College]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Quebec}} || '''1 June 2016''' || [[McGill University]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mcgill.ca/senate/files/senate/honorary_degree_recipients_alpha_list_updated_nov._2016.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317144411/https://www.mcgill.ca/senate/files/senate/honorary_degree_recipients_alpha_list_updated_nov._2016.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 17, 2017|title=Wayback Machine|date=March 17, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Alberta}} || '''28 April 2017''' || [[Lethbridge College]] || Bachelor of Applied Arts <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fortmacleodgazette.com/2017/chief-justice-of-canada-to-receive-honorary-degree-from-lethbridge-college/|title=Chief Justice to receive honorary degree Lethbridge College - Fort Macleod Gazette|website=www.fortmacleodgazette.com|accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://lethbridgeherald.com/news/lethbridge-news/2017/03/10/college-to-honour-chief-justice-mclachlin/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=May 13, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170314012526/http://lethbridgeherald.com/news/lethbridge-news/2017/03/10/college-to-honour-chief-justice-mclachlin/ |archive-date=March 14, 2017 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>  \n|-\n| {{Flagu|Newfoundland and Labrador}} || '''19 October 2017''' || [[Memorial University of Newfoundland]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mun.ca/convocation/previous/Fall_2017_SJ.pdf|format=PDF|title=FALL CONVOCATION 2017|website=Mun.ca|accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n| {{Flagu|Ontario}} || '''2019''' || [[University of Ontario Institute of Technology]] || Doctor of Laws (LL.D.)  <ref>https://uoit.ca/convocation/honorary-degrees/2019/the-right-honourable-beverley-mclachlin.php</ref>\n|- \n|}\n{{Expand list|date=May 2015}}\n\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"  style=\"margin:auto; margin:1em 1em 1em 0; background:white; border:1px #0047ab solid; border-collapse:collapse;\"\n|- style=\"background:white;\"\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<span style=\"color:black;\">Ribbon bar of Beverley McLachlin</span>\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|ribbon=VOStJ ribbon.png}}\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|ribbon=Canada125 ribbon.png}}\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|ribbon=QEII Golden Jubilee Medal ribbon.png}}\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|ribbon=QEII_Diamond_Jubilee_Medal_ribbon.png}}\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|ribbon=Legion Honneur Commandeur ribbon.svg}}\n|}\n\n* [[Order of Saint John (chartered 1888)|Order of Saint John \u2013 Commander]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/beverley-mclachlin/|title=Beverley McLachlin|last=Makin|first=Kirk|work=The Canadian Encyclopedia|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[125th Anniversary of the Confederation of Canada Medal]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n* [[Queen Elizabeth II Golden Jubilee Medal]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n* [[Queen Elizabeth II Diamond Jubilee Medal]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n* [[Legion of Honour|Legion of Honour \u2013 {{lang|fr|Commandeur}}]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n==See Also==\n* [[List of Supreme Court of Canada cases (McLachlin Court)]]\n\n==Books==\n* {{cite book |last=McLachlin  |first=Beverley M.|last2= Wallace|first2=Wilfred J.  |date=1987 |title=The Canadian Law of Architecture and Engineering  |location=Toronto |publisher=Butterworths}}\n* {{cite book |last=McLachlin  |first=Beverley  |date=2018 |title=Full Disclosure: A Novel |location=Toronto |publisher=Simon & Schuster Canada}}\n* {{cite book |last=McLachlin  |first=Beverley  |date=2019 |title=Truth Be Told: My Journey Through Life and the Law |location=Toronto |publisher=Simon & Schuster Canada}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{CanadaSupremeCourtbio|beverley-mclachlin}}\n* [http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/en/article/beverley-mclachlin/ The Canadian Encyclopedia - Beverley McLachlin]\n* [http://www.charterofrights.ca/language.php Fundamental Freedoms: The Charter of Rights and Freedoms] \u2013 Charter of Rights website with video, audio and the Charter in over 20 languages\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-prec|can}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Stephen Harper]]|as= Former [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Canadian order of precedence|Order of Precedence of Canada]]<br>''{{small|as Former [[Chief Justice of Canada|Chief Justice]]}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[George Furey]]|as=[[Speaker of the Senate of Canada]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{CanadaCJs}}\n{{Dickson-court}}\n{{Lamer-court}}\n{{McLachlin-court}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McLachlin, Beverley}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian legal scholars]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian women judges]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of Canada]]\n[[Category:Commandeurs of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of St John]]\n[[Category:Judges in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Lawyers in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Municipal District of Pincher Creek No. 9]]\n[[Category:University of Alberta alumni]]\n[[Category:University of British Columbia faculty]]\n[[Category:Women chief justices]]\n[[Category:Canadian women lawyers]]\n[[Category:University of Alberta Faculty of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian novelists]]\n[[Ca